
Send TS packets using Reliable Internet Stream Transport (RIST)

Usage: tsp -O rist [options]

Parameters:

  One or more RIST URL's. A RIST URL may include tuning parameters in addition
  to the address and port. See https://code.videolan.
  org/rist/librist/-/wikis/LibRIST%20Documentation for more details.

Options:

  -b value
  --buffer-size value
      Default buffer size in bytes for packet retransmissions.

  -e
  --enforce-burst
      Enforce that the number of TS packets per UDP packet is exactly what is
      specified in option --packet-burst. By default, this is only a maximum
      value.

  --help
      Display this help text.

  -n
  --null-packet-deletion
      Enable null packet deletion. The receiver needs to support this.

  --packet-burst value
      Specifies the maximum number of TS packets per UDP packet. The default is
      7, the maximum is 128.

  -p name
  --profile name
      Specify the RIST profile (main profile by default).
      Must be one of "advanced", "main", "simple".

  --version[=value]
      Display the TSDuck and RIST library version numbers and immediately
      exits.
      Must be one of "all", "bitrate", "compiler", "date", "dektec", "http",
      "integer", "long", "nsis", "short", "srt", "system".

